WHO   — Coach Bud Kilmer — the win-at-all-costs tyrant
WHAT  — The villain and the town's god: the man who puts the banner over the boy and gets away with it because he wins.
WHERE — VBL · Varsity Blues (1999)  Framework inputs: Varsity Blues (1999, dir. Brian Robbins, MTV Films/Paramount); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because every sports movie needs the dark father — the adult who values the scoreboard over the child.
HOW   — By shooting up injuries, hiding concussions, and trading on a legend the town is too grateful to question.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Twenty-two districts buys a lot of silence. The W is the only truth — until the boys decide it isn't.

